A '''hymenophore''' refers to the [[hymenium]]-bearing structure of a [[fungi|fungal]] [[fruiting body]]. Hymenophores can be smooth surfaces, [[lamellae (mycology)|lamellae]], folds, tubes, or teeth. The term was coined by [[Robert Hooke]] in 1665.
